column5: Hubby and I are looking for a new spot, we went to Port Severn the last few times but have not caught anything worth hooking.  We would like to find a place less than an hour from Victoria Harbor, a place where we can rent for up to 4 people.  Was looking at Honey Harbour, but is it to populated? If you have any ideas, sure would be appreciated.  Lorissa

Waubaushene, about 10 minutes from Victoria Harbour...I think there's a couple of places there to rent a boat if that's what you mean, one that comes to mind is pier 69.  You can fish the channel, Matchedash Bay, and go into Hogs bay (victoria Harbour)...all kinds of places right there...  Maureen

In Victoria Harbour there is a boat rental place. $65.00 for the whole day. $25 deposit which you get back when you return.  I cant recall how to get there but the phone number is 1-705-534-7101 Kevin is the guy. Its right next to some good fishing waters.

Thanx Guys  Unfortunately we have pretty much fished that out, I guess it is time to fit in looking at the topo map....  Appreciate the effort......  Lorissa
honey harbour is quite poppulated but its very nice.was there many years ago we caught tons of 2 and 3 pound smallies in 10-12 feet of water i believe it was near midland.
Here's one I figure you haven't tried yet:  http://members.ozemail.com.au/~kamosida/Japan.htm
